					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2238524#post-2797939</guid>
				<title>Thanks, Attribution, and Others</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2238524/spc-2000#post-2797939</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 22 Apr 2017 01:46:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MrWrong</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2039383</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>As always, allow me to express thanks to all who have read the article while it was a draft and express their impressions of it.</p> <p>Image sources are as follows:</p> <ul> <li>Image 1 by The Doctor is IN of Flickr (<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/49024304@N00/4392162615">https://www.flickr.com/photos/49024304@N00/4392162615</a>) under CC BY 2.0</li> <li>Image 2 by Philippe Guillaume of Wikimedia Commons (<a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Squatina_squatina_tenerife.jpg">https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Squatina_squatina_tenerife.jpg</a>) under CC BY 2.0</li> </ul> <p>This article also features SCP-1373 (Laser Shark Fetus) by Voct (originally written by minmin)</p> <p>Well, given that the Shark Punching Center/Centre is a rather out-there concept, a more down-to-earth article about them should be in order.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>And seriously, if the Foundation/Centre figured out cloning, it is the biggest scientific breakthrough&#8230; and they choose to make human-shaped guinea pigs? Why not hold back the decline of a certain superorder of fishes?</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
